{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Preheat oven to 180°C and line two baking trays with baking paper then set aside.","Place butter, sugar and golden syrup in mixing bowl then heat <b>5 min\/80°C\/speed 1<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl and around blade with spatula.","Add flour, ginger, mixed spice, cinnamon, bicarbonate of soda and salt then mix <b>2 min\/speed 2<b>.","Spoon out 1 Tbsp-sized pieces of dough and roll into balls then place on prepared baking trays at least 3 cm apart. Bake for 10-12 minutes (180°C) until golden brown (see tip).","Leave biscuits to cool on trays for a few minutes before transferring to a wire rack to cool completely. Serve or store in an airtight container for up to 5 days."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["100 g unsalted butter, diced","100 g golden caster sugar","60 g golden syrup","175 g self-raising flour","1 tsp ground ginger","¼ tsp ground mixed spice","¼ tsp ground cinnamon","¼ tsp bicarbonate of soda","1 pinch fine sea salt"]}],"id":"r94618","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-BfgcGsPpZ_k\/XZWqR6OEs0I\/AAAAAAAAfVk\/xsIQnh__IR4urBJH1iiy9s8Hxyju-N85wCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_HhjTPSYoNBKAmqYu.png","title":"Cornish Fairings","publishedAt":"2015-12-17T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"0.9 g","fat":"4.7 g","uom":"per 1 pieces","carbohydrates":"16 g","calories":"461 kJ \/ 110 kcal"},"usefulItems":"wire rack, 2 baking trays and baking paper, air-tight container, oven","hintsAndTricks":["The biscuits should have a cracked appearance that occurs during cooking. If biscuits still look smooth after 5 minutes, remove from oven and carefully bang the baking trays on the counter top to make the biscuits crack and spread, before returning to oven to finish baking.","These traditional ginger biscuits are commonly found in Cornwall. The term ‘fairing’ originally applied to any edible treat sold at a fair, although it is now synonymous with these crunchy, cracked ginger biscuits."],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","35m","18 pieces"]}